# 🔹 Huffman Coding

Used for **lossless data compression**.

Examples:

* ZIP files
* PNG images
* PDF compression

---

## Idea

Characters with **higher frequency get shorter binary codes**.

Characters with **lower frequency get longer binary codes**.

---

### Example

| Character | Frequency |
| --------- | --------: |
| A         |        45 |
| B         |        13 |
| C         |        12 |
| D         |        16 |
| E         |         9 |
| F         |         5 |

Build a **Min Heap**, repeatedly combine the two nodes with the smallest frequencies until one tree remains.

---

## Properties

✅ Prefix-free codes

✅ No ambiguity in decoding

---

## Complexity

Building the heap:

[
O(n)
]

Repeated operations:

[
O(n\log n)
]

